detaileddescription.para:
console_logger is a small, dependency free C++ logging library with ANSI color support. It's designed to be an include-and-use logger that helps to create uniform output for you and your users. No objects are created, meaning that logging is as simple as: logger::input("Pleaseenterafilepath");
logger::info("Filecreatedsuccessfuly!");
 No global state and no configuration to get started.

sect1.para:
Include the header: #include<console/logger/console_logger.h>
 Log from anywhere: logger::info("Applicationstarted");
logger::warning("Lowmemory");
logger::error("Failedtoopenfile");
